acquired Cooper Automotive. Initially there was some uncertainty as to the entity, which had had dealings with the complainant. The first respondent, after further investigation and subsequent to the joinder of the 2nd and 4th respondents, determined that 
the conduct contained in the complaint occurred after Ferodo's marketing and sales operations had been transferred to the Federal Mogul Group. Accordingly, counsel for the respondents conceded that the first respondent was properly a respondent in this mat
ter.   }}}
