owever, from the perspective of the enforcement of the Competition Act, what is significant is Erasmus\'92 allegation that the respondent\'92s action to reduce his rebate arose out of his participation in a price war \'96 in short, Erasmus alleges that because he o
ffered products purchased from Federal Mogul at a price lower than that imposed by his supplier, his rebate and, crucially, his margins, were cut, rendering his business non-viable.    }
